{"updated_at": "2012-08-28T11:36:14Z", "repo": "rails", "created_at": "2012-08-28T11:35:57Z", "owner": "rails", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/8088639", "id": 8088639, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/7464", "issue_id": 7464, "user": {"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paneq/repos", "type": "User", "html_url": "https://github.com/paneq", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paneq/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paneq/subscriptions", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paneq/following{/other_user}", "gravatar_id": "9b81cae1fb43808ac23a2188258ca9e4", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paneq/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/paneq", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paneq/gists{/gist_id}", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/9b81cae1fb43808ac23a2188258ca9e4?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F180bb054f1a36e1777b05a0664a7eb71.png", "id": 65587, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paneq/events{/privacy}", "login": "paneq", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paneq/received_events", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paneq/followers"}, "body": "Let's just say that we find out that IE6 is doing something stupid. Maybe we do not care as this browser is not supported in our project and we would like to drop workarounds in favor of following the http spec. What do you think about adding config for browser compatibility into rails ex.:\n\n```ruby\n  config.browsers.ie = 8\n```\n\nThis could mean that we want to support `IE >= 8` and disable hacks for ie6 and ie7.\n\nCould that be helpful ?", "_id": {"$oid": "5237fb62bd3543c15100b7cc"}, "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7464#issuecomment-8088639"}
